                            <comment id="14032125" author="thartmann" created="Wed, 14 Dec 2016 01:57:06 -0800"  >Thanks, Mikael! Maybe we should consider removing it then. I&amp;#39;m investigating a crash that is caused by an oop pointing to a zapped heap region (JDK-8169934) and wanted to enable this flag to get additional verification.</comment>
                            <comment id="14032122" author="mgerdin" created="Wed, 14 Dec 2016 01:53:06 -0800"  >+CheckMemoryInitialization is a notproduct flag so it&amp;#39;s only available in fastdebug builds.&lt;br/&gt;
I tried this flag on JDK 7 GA (1.7.0-b147) and all GCs except CMS crash with this flag when running java -version.&lt;br/&gt;
This has been broken for a long time.</comment>
